5:[["$","$L10",null,{}],["$","main",null,{"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto","children":[["$","$L11",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors mb-10","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-arrow-left w-4 h-4","aria-hidden":true,"children":[["$","path","1l729n",{"d":"m12 19-7-7 7-7"}],["$","path","x3x0zl",{"d":"M19 12H5"}],"$undefined"]}],"Field Notes"]}],["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs font-medium text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400 mb-3","children":"Operations"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 balance","children":"Felipe Reviews Your Intake Workflow"}],["$","time",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500","children":"Mar 19, 2025"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-like","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 italic mb-4","children":"Felipe has been coordinating animal intake at a mid-size rescue for six years. He has seen every intake workflow mistake at least twice. Here are his notes."}],["$","hr","1",{"className":"my-8 border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800"}],["$","h3","2",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"\"We do intake on paper and enter it later\""}],["$","p","3",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"I understand why you do this. The animal is in front of you, you're trying to get them comfortable, you don't have time to type. The paper form is fast."}}],["$","p","4",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The problem is \"later\" doesn't happen. Or it happens three days later, when you can't remember what the intake volunteer told you about the dog's history. Or it happens halfway, and you have half the record in paper and half in the system."}}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"What actually works: a phone or tablet at intake, with a form that takes 4 minutes to fill out completely. Yes, even when the animal is distressed. The 4 minutes now saves 40 minutes of reconstruction later."}}],["$","h3","6",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"\"We have a separate system for medical records\""}],["$","p","7",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Every organization that has a separate medical records system has a coordination problem. The animal's intake status is in System A. Their vaccine history is in System B. When the adoption coordinator wants to know if an animal is cleared for adoption, they have to check two places, and one of them usually has stale data."}}],["$","p","8",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Unified records exist. Use them."}}],["$","h3","9",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"\"Our foster coordinator keeps track of placements\""}],["$","p","10",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Your foster coordinator is doing great work. She also knows things that aren't written down anywhere, and when she takes a vacation or — inevitably — burns out and steps back, those placements exist only in her head."}}],"$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19"]}],"$L1a"]}]}]}],"$L1b"]
12:["$","p","11",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"A system doesn't replace your foster coordinator. It makes her replaceable in the best sense: someone else can step in without losing the thread of 15 active placements."}}]
13:["$","h3","12",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"\"We don't track outcomes\""}]
14:["$","p","13",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"This one is expensive. When you apply for a grant, they want to know your adoption rate. Your reunification rate. Your average length of stay. If you've been tracking outcomes — even informally — you have numbers. If you haven't, you're estimating, and funders can tell."}}]
15:["$","p","14",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Outcome tracking is a 2-minute step at the end of each adoption or reunion. It's worth it."}}]
16:["$","h3","15",{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3","children":"\"We'll fix the workflow when things calm down\""}]
17:["$","p","16",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Things don't calm down. Intake season is always either just ending or just beginning. The fix-it window that you're waiting for doesn't exist."}}]
18:["$","p","17",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The organizations that have good workflows built them in the middle of chaos, because that's when you most need them."}}]
19:["$","p","18",{"className":"text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Start with the minimum: animal record, status, location, task for next action. Get that right. Everything else comes later."}}]
